## 8. 🟡 No HTTPS Enforcement (OWASP A02 / Transport Security)

**Finding:** The server listens on a plain TCP port (3000) with no TLS. Credentials and session tokens sent over plain HTTP are trivially interceptable.

**Fix:** In production, always terminate TLS — either at the app level or via a reverse proxy (nginx, Caddy, a load balancer). If terminating at the app:

```js
const https = require('https');
const fs = require('fs');

const options = {
  key:  fs.readFileSync(process.env.TLS_KEY_PATH),
  cert: fs.readFileSync(process.env.TLS_CERT_PATH),
};

https.createServer(options, app).listen(443);

// Redirect HTTP → HTTPS
const http = require('http');
http.createServer((req, res) => {
  res.writeHead(301, { Location: `https://${req.headers.host}${req.url}` });
  res.end();
}).listen(80);
```

Also set the HSTS header via `helmet` once on HTTPS:

```js
helmet({ hsts: { maxAge: 31536000, includeSubDomains: true } })
```

